ClientResponses.Response:
Hey, we’ve recently added roast and ground coffee ground 10 times finer to our new blend of NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. Find out more by watching this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

Results.ReviewText: Having bought Gold Blend for th last thirty years I was under the impression that’s I knew what it tasted like. However, with no warning on the packaging, the contents of this pack is nothing like the coffee that I remember. Gold Blend is rich, smooth and strong. This is weak, gritty and unpleasant. If you are going to change a well established recipe you should at least inform your loyal customers. As anyone got any recommendations of a coffee that is more like the original than this repellant substitute.
Results.Title: Mis-sold coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know what you think of the changes we've made. Please be assured that we haven't added anything else to the recipe apart from Micro Ground coffee during the change. We'd suggest seeking medical advice for if you are feeling unwell.

Results.ReviewText: Thus us absolutely horrible since it has changed. We used to drink two jars a week as there are six people here who only drink coffee. One is gluten intolerant and it's made her ill so it must be mixed with the cheap barley substitute. It's now undrinkable so thanks nescafe.

Results.ReviewText: This Nescafe' Gold Blend has been our families favourite coffee for many years, - (and love the great new jar by the way). One of my daugher's friends asked her which coffee her mum used because she said it was the best she'd tasted, of course it was Gold Blend (made this way). Always buy two at a time, - never want to run out. Change the jar by all means, - but please never change this great Coffee.

My first encounter with it left me thinking I'd accidentally bought a supermarket's cheap "own brand" by mistake.  Having purchased again (ensuring that I have definitely bought Gold Blend) I am really disappointed with what you've done to it.  The coffee has a bitter aftertaste and leaves a horrible black powdery sludge in the bottom of the cup.  If I wanted barista style coffee -  I would buy it!   

I can't express how disappointed I am, I used to really look forward to my cups of coffee but this new recipe leaves me feeling slightly nauseous.  This new recipe is "Simply Vile!".  Our family of 5 will be looking for an alternative.

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend has been my mainstay instant coffee for many years.  I always enjoyed the rich, mellow taste and the smell, when opening a new jar, was enticing.  I do't knwo what you've done to it but the smell has gone, the taste is harsher and, perhaps mercifully, weaker.  There are now also grains at left at the bottom of the cup.  I expect this in ground cofee but not in soluble instant coffee.  They add nothing and are, presumably, there to mimic fresh ground coffee.  Believe me no is fooled.

It's great on its own as a dark rich coffee or with a splash of milk for that curl up comfort coffee either way you'll not be disappointed with gold blend in my opinion it's one of nescafe's finest and wholly recommend it to anyone that listens
